    a2: 'Gas safety is the starting point for every Roncesvalles diagnostic. We check all burner valve connections and the main gas supply fitting for leaks before touching anything else. We then test every surface burner: spark electrode tip condition, burner cap alignment — older Maytag and Kenmore models sometimes develop slightly warped caps that disrupt the spark path — burner port inspection for residue clogging, and spark module output voltage. We test the oven bake igniter by measuring its current draw: a failing igniter glows orange but draws below the threshold needed to open the gas safety valve. We check the oven thermostat accuracy with a calibrated probe thermometer against the set temperature. Broil circuit function is also tested. All findings go into a written, itemized quote — specific parts, specific costs, no surprises. The $119 is fully waived when you proceed with the repair. Our technicians carry igniter electrodes, bake igniters, spark modules, and burner components for Maytag and Kenmore on every service van, covering the most common Roncesvalles repair scenarios.',
    q3: 'What are the most common stove problems in Roncesvalles homes?',
    a3: 'Roncesvalles is a Polish and European community in Victorian semi-detached homes, and gas ranges are the strong cultural preference — heavy baking, roasting, and stovetop cooking are daily activities in many households here. This intensive use pattern creates a specific and consistent set of service calls. Igniter electrode wear is the top call: years of daily use erode the electrode tip, and the burner starts clicking repeatedly without lighting, or requires three or four tries before the gas catches. Bake igniter failure is closely behind — the oven igniter glows but has weakened to the point where it cannot open the gas safety valve, so the oven never heats even though the surface burners work fine. Burner port clogging is the third most common issue, particularly on older Kenmore models where years of European cooking have left residue in the small ports around the burner head. Older Maytag and Kenmore gas ranges from the mid-2000s are the dominant brands in Roncesvalles, and our technicians know these models well.',
    q4: 'How does same-day stove repair work in Roncesvalles?',
    a4: 'Call (437) 524-1053 or book online for Roncesvalles and we confirm a same-day 2-4 hour arrival window. Roncesvalles is in our west Toronto service corridor. The technician calls 30 minutes ahead of arrival. Any report of gas smell triggers a priority dispatch — turn off the range, open windows, and do not use the stove until we arrive. Gas safety check is the first step on every gas stove call: we verify no active leak before any inspection or disassembly. Our vans carry igniter electrodes, bake igniters, spark modules, burner caps, and common gas valve components for Maytag and Kenmore. After diagnosing the fault we present a written quote and wait for your approval before beginning any repair. The typical Roncesvalles repair — igniter electrode or bake igniter — takes 45-90 minutes and is completed in a single visit. We test every surface burner lit and cycle the oven to temperature with a probe thermometer before leaving. The 90-day parts and labour warranty starts from the repair date.',
    q5: 'What should I prepare before the stove technician arrives in Roncesvalles?',
    a5: 'Safety first: if there has been any gas smell near the range, turn all knobs to OFF, close the gas shut-off valve behind the range, open windows, and flag it when booking. For a standard gas repair, turn the stove off and let it cool. Remove the burner grates and burner caps from the cooktop surface — on older Maytag and Kenmore models this is usually straightforward and gives the technician direct access to the burner heads and igniter electrodes. Leave any visible residue or corrosion in place so the technician can assess it as part of the diagnosis. If the oven is the problem, turn off the oven and leave the oven door slightly ajar to allow any residual heat to dissipate before the technician arrives. Pull the range slightly away from the wall — Victorian semi-detached kitchens in Roncesvalles can be narrow, but even a few inches of clearance helps with rear panel access and checking the gas line fitting. Write down which burner or oven function has failed and what happens when you try to use it. Locate the model number inside the oven door frame.',
