    a4: 'Call (437) 524-1053 or book online for Wychwood and we confirm a same-day 2-4 hour arrival window. Wychwood is in our north-west Toronto service area around Davenport and Christie. The technician calls 30 minutes before arrival. Gas safety check is the first step on every gas stove call: we verify no active leak before any disassembly. For any gas smell, the call is dispatched as a priority. Our vans carry igniter electrodes, bake igniters, spark modules for gas, and surface elements, bake elements, and thermistors for electric — covering the most common faults in both the gas and electric Kenmore and GE models found throughout Wychwood. After diagnosis we present a written quote for your approval before any work begins. Most Wychwood repairs are completed in a single visit. Heritage home kitchens in Wychwood can be compact, but our technicians work with tight spaces regularly. After repair, all burners are tested lit and the oven is cycled to temperature and verified with a probe thermometer. The 90-day parts and labour warranty starts from the repair date.',
    q5: 'What should I prepare before the stove technician arrives in Wychwood?',
    a5: 'For a gas stove in a Wychwood heritage home: if there is any gas smell, turn all burner knobs to OFF, close the gas shut-off valve behind the range, open windows, and flag it when booking. For a standard gas repair, turn the stove off and remove burner grates and caps from the cooktop to give the technician immediate access to the igniter electrodes and burner heads. Note which specific burner or oven function has failed and describe exactly what it does when you try to use it. For electric ranges: turn the stove off and allow all surfaces to cool. Clear the cooktop. If the oven is running too hot or too cold — a common Kenmore thermistor issue in Wychwood — write down approximately how far off the temperature is and whether it runs hot or cold, since this points specifically to the temperature sensor. If there are error codes on the display, photograph them before unplugging. Locate the model number sticker inside the oven door frame. Wychwood heritage home kitchens are often compact — pull the range as far from the wall as the space allows to give the technician working room for rear panel access.',
